communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any invoices or payment records relating to the company SpyCloud (SpyCloud.com), as well as any documents relating to any free trials of SpyCloud the LBPD may have participated in.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Greg Buhl

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Amber Alert Information
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Amber Alerts disseminated by your agency for the years 2012 to present. Please include any information provided by the requesting agency for those alerts.
Amber Alerts rejected for dissemination submitted to your agency for the years 2012 to present. Please include any information provided by the requesting agency and the reason for denial.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Albert Winfrey

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

The application for rental registration for 1405 Cypress St. 
Copies of any and all health and safety inspections from 2010 to present with any resulting citations or violations.
Copies of any and all receipts for payment of health and safety inspections from 2010 to present.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Albert Winfrey
